# articles-system

## Description
This is a simple web-API for managing posts. This allows CRUD functions of posts

## Needed Stacks
1. Golang (Gin)
2. PostgreSQL

## Installation
1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Bainandhika/post-system
   cd post-system
   ```
2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   go mod tidy
   ```
3. Prepare the .env file:
   Create a .env file in the project root directory with the following content:
   ```env
   APP_HOST=localhost
   APP_PORT=8000
   APP_LOG_PATH=logs

   DATABASE_HOST=localhost
   DATABASE_PORT=5432
   DATABASE_USER=admin
   DATABASE_PASSWORD=
   DATABASE_NAME=post_system
   ```
4. Build the executable:
   ```bash
   go build
   ```
5. Make sure PostgreSQL is running database is already created. Then run the application:
   ```bash
   ./main
   ```
6. Log files stored at post-system/logs

